dot("$F_2$", F[2], S);
dot("$P$", P, S);
label("$Q$", Q, NE);
[/asy]

Let $Q = (a,b).$  Then $F_2 P$ has equation
\[\frac{y - 3}{x} = \frac{b - 3}{a},\]which simplifies to $ax - (b - 3) y + 3b - 9 = 0.$  Substituting into $\frac{x^2}{49} + \frac{y^2}{33} = 1,$ we get
\[\frac{x^2}{49} + \frac{(ax - (b - 3) y + 3b - 9)^2}{33} = 1.\]This simplifies to
\[(33a^2 + 49) x^2 - 66(b - 3)(3b - 9) x + 33(b - 3)^2 + 49(3b - 9)^2 - 33(3b - 9)^2 = 0.\]This quadratic in $x$ has a double root at $x = 0,$ so
\[(33a^2 + 49) x^2 - 66(b - 3)(3b - 9) x = 0.\]Since $x = 0$ is not a solution, we can divide both sides by $x,$ to get
\[(33a^2 + 49) x - 66(b - 3)(3b - 9) = 0.\]Then $x = \frac{66(b - 3)(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49}.$  Substituting into $ax - (b - 3) y + 3b - 9 = 0,$ we get
\[\frac{66(b - 3)(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} \cdot a - (b - 3) y + 3b - 9 = 0.\]This simplifies to
\[\frac{66a(b - 3)(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} - (b - 3) y + 3b - 9 = 0.\]Then
\[(b - 3) y = \frac{66a(b - 3)(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} + 3b - 9.\]Since $b - 3 \neq 0,$ we can divide both sides by $b - 3,$ to get
\[y = \frac{66a(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} + 3.\]Substituting into $x^2 + y^2 = 6y - 9,$ we get
\[x^2 + \left( \frac{66a(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} + 3 \right)^2 = 6 \left( \frac{66a(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} + 3 \right) - 9.\]This simplifies to
\[(33a^2 + 49) x^2 + 66a(3b - 9) x + 33(3b - 9)^2 + 49(33a^2 + 49) - 33(33a^2 + 49) = 0.\]This quadratic in $x$ has a double root at $x = 0,$ so
\[(33a^2 + 49) x^2 + 66a(3b - 9) x = 0.\]Since $x = 0$ is not a solution, we can divide both sides by $x,$ to get
\[(33a^2 + 49) x + 66a(3b - 9) = 0.\]Then $x = -\frac{66a(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49}.$  Substituting into $\frac{x^2}{49} + \frac{y^2}{33} = 1,$ we get
\[\frac{\left( -\frac{66a(3b - 9)}{33a^2 + 49} \right)^2}{49} + \frac{y^2}{33} = 1.\]This simplifies to
\[\frac{66^2 a^2 (3b - 9)^2}{(33a^2 + 49)^2} + \frac{y^2}{33} = 1.\]Then
\[\frac{66^2 a^2 (3b - 9)^2}{(33a^2 + 49)^2} + \frac{33(3b - 9)^2}{33} = 1.\]This simplifies to
\[\frac{66^2 a^2 (3b - 9)^2 + (3b - 9)^2 (33a^2 + 49)^2}{(33a^2 + 49)^2} = 1.\]This simplifies to
\[66^2 a^2 + (33a^2 + 49)^2 = (33a^2 + 49)^2.\]This simplifies to $66^2 a^2 = 0.$  Hence, $a = 0.$  Then $x = 0,$ so $Q = (0,b).$  Substituting into $x^2 + y^2 = 6y - 9,$ we get
\[b^2 = 6b - 9.\]This simplifies to $b^2 - 6b + 9 = 0,$ which factors as $(b - 3)^2 = 0.$  Hence, $b = 3,$ so $Q = (0,3).$

